<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,594,1411]" box="[151,766,594,619]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">
Body length (incl. tegmen): ♂, 
<quantity box="[502,633,594,619]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.75" metricValueMax="8.8" metricValueMin="6.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" unit="mm" value="7.75" valueMax="8.8" valueMin="6.7">6.7–8.8mm</quantity>
; ♀, 
<quantity box="[680,766,595,619]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" unit="mm" value="8.8">8.8 mm</quantity>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,594,1411]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Head and thorax stramineous dorsally. Vertex with yellow band anteriorly margined dark brown. Face yellow with clypeus, clypellus, antennal pit and basal segment of antenna, dark brown. Pronotum with narrow yellow band anteriorly, lateral margin brown. Forewing pale brownish hyaline, veins brown with white maculation. Female pregenital segment with posterior medial lobe dark brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,594,1411]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[277,343,774,799]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1601,1623]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,268,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,261,1535]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Drabescus quadrispinosus sp. nov. A. adult, dorsal view; B. face, ventral view; C. female terminalia, ventral view; D. left side of pygofer, lateral view; E. valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; F. aedeagus and connective, lateral view; G. aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224346/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">
Fig. 
<number box="[333,343,775,799]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A) slightly wider than pronotum; fore-margin with few fine transverse striations. Vertex with midlength slightly longer than length next to eyes. Face (
<figureCitation box="[821,888,810,835]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1601,1623]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,268,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,261,1535]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Drabescus quadrispinosus sp. nov. A. adult, dorsal view; B. face, ventral view; C. female terminalia, ventral view; D. left side of pygofer, lateral view; E. valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; F. aedeagus and connective, lateral view; G. aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224346/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">
Fig. 
<number box="[877,888,811,835]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B) with antennal ledge strong; transverse ridge present between antennal ledges; laterofrontal suture extended to lateral margin of corresponding ocellus; clypeus with longitudinal striations. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[596,659,882,907]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1601,1623]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,268,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,261,1535]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Drabescus quadrispinosus sp. nov. A. adult, dorsal view; B. face, ventral view; C. female terminalia, ventral view; D. left side of pygofer, lateral view; E. valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; F. aedeagus and connective, lateral view; G. aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224346/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">
Fig. 
<number box="[649,659,883,907]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A) with lateral margin short; transversely striate. Fore tibia flattened dorsally. 
<collectingCountry box="[253,309,918,943]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">Hind</collectingCountry>
femur with apical setae 
<number box="[584,601,919,943]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[620,631,919,943]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" value="1.0">1</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,594,1411]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">
Male pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[371,436,954,979]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1601,1623]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,268,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,261,1535]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Drabescus quadrispinosus sp. nov. A. adult, dorsal view; B. face, ventral view; C. female terminalia, ventral view; D. left side of pygofer, lateral view; E. valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; F. aedeagus and connective, lateral view; G. aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224346/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">
Fig. 
<number box="[426,436,955,979]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
D) tapered to narrow apex posteriorly, with moderately long process ventroposteriorly. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[347,409,990,1015]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1601,1623]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,268,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,261,1535]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Drabescus quadrispinosus sp. nov. A. adult, dorsal view; B. face, ventral view; C. female terminalia, ventral view; D. left side of pygofer, lateral view; E. valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; F. aedeagus and connective, lateral view; G. aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224346/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">
Fig. 
<number box="[399,409,991,1015]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
E) elongate, triangular with several short fine setae basolaterally. Style (
<figureCitation box="[1215,1277,990,1015]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1601,1623]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,268,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,261,1535]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Drabescus quadrispinosus sp. nov. A. adult, dorsal view; B. face, ventral view; C. female terminalia, ventral view; D. left side of pygofer, lateral view; E. valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; F. aedeagus and connective, lateral view; G. aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224346/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">
Fig. 
<number box="[1267,1277,991,1015]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
F) with apical process digitate, moderately long; lateral lobe very short. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[942,1016,1026,1051]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1601,1623]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,268,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,261,1535]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Drabescus quadrispinosus sp. nov. A. adult, dorsal view; B. face, ventral view; C. female terminalia, ventral view; D. left side of pygofer, lateral view; E. valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; F. aedeagus and connective, lateral view; G. aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224346/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">
Figs. 
<number box="[1006,1016,1027,1051]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
F, 
<number box="[1047,1057,1027,1051]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" value="1.0">1</number>
G) short. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1294,1361,1026,1051]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1601,1623]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,268,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,261,1535]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Drabescus quadrispinosus sp. nov. A. adult, dorsal view; B. face, ventral view; C. female terminalia, ventral view; D. left side of pygofer, lateral view; E. valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; F. aedeagus and connective, lateral view; G. aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224346/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">
Figs 
<number box="[1351,1361,1027,1051]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
F, 
<number box="[1393,1403,1027,1051]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" value="1.0">1</number>
G) with shaft curved ventrally, with pair of long processes basally on each side, inner process of each pair narrower.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,594,1411]" box="[199,1333,1098,1123]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">
Female pregenital sternite (
<figureCitation box="[505,567,1098,1123]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1601,1623]" captionTargetBox="[167,1421,268,1528]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,261,1535]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Drabescus quadrispinosus sp. nov. A. adult, dorsal view; B. face, ventral view; C. female terminalia, ventral view; D. left side of pygofer, lateral view; E. valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; F. aedeagus and connective, lateral view; G. aedeagus, connective and style, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224346/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="143">
Fig. 
<number box="[557,567,1099,1123]" pageId="2" pageNumber="143" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C) deeply incised each side of midline forming distinct medial lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
